@node asctime
@section @code{asctime}---format time as string
@findex asctime
@findex _asctime_r
@strong{Synopsis}
@example
#include <time.h>
char *asctime(const struct tm *@var{clock});
char *_asctime_r(const struct tm *@var{clock}, char *@var{buf});

@end example
@strong{Description}@*
Format the time value at @var{clock} into a string of the form
@smallexample
 Wed Jun 15 11:38:07 1988\n\0
@end smallexample
The string is generated in a static buffer; each call to @code{asctime}
overwrites the string generated by previous calls.

@*
@strong{Returns}@*
A pointer to the string containing a formatted timestamp.

@*
@strong{Portability}@*
ANSI C requires @code{asctime}.

@code{asctime} requires no supporting OS subroutines.

@*
